-- Japanese Bought Net 663.1 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   I s a a c   A q u i n o
-- 2013-01-30T23:55:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-30/japanese-bought-net-663-1-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended Jan. 25 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 663.1 billion yen ($7.3 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 254.1 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 66 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 343 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 228.8 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 248.6 billion yen in stocks, and sold 521.5 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net sale 501.6
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
Isaac Aquino in Tokyo at   iaquino1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
